body:
@rizac : Well 2017 is not 2020, so until then, Python 2.x compatibility must remain :smile: 

However, I think `unicode_literals` is your best way to go, as it works just fine with your code, and if it's centering around a `numpy` array creation, that's something that's out of our control I think at this point.    The `ascii` character set is something that is beyond `pandas`.

True, you don't get `bytes`, but at least the code works, and you can always reconvert elements back to `bytes` if you need them to be so subsequently when handling them.
